r the Scottish mathematician Colin Maclaurin. The Maclaurin series of a fun=
ction f(x) up to order n may be found using Series[f, {x, 0, n}]. The nth t=
erm of a Maclaurin series of a function f can be computed in the Wolfram La=
nguage using SeriesCoefficient[f, {x, 0, n}] and is given by the inverse Z-=
transform  a_n=3DZ^(-1)[f(1/x)](n).  (2)   Maclaurin series are a type of s=
eries...">
